### Templates and prompts usage

- **Blocks**
  - Reusable content units in `templates/blocks/`; names end with `-block.md`
  - Compose larger documents by including relevant blocks
  - Example: [templates/blocks/title-block.md](mdc:templates/blocks/title-block.md)

- **Outputs**
  - Final artifact templates in `templates/outputs/`
  - Example: [templates/outputs/agent-template.md](mdc:templates/outputs/agent-template.md)

- **Context templates**
  - Structural definitions in `templates/context/` (e.g., feature, role, actor)
  - Example: [templates/context/feature-template.md](mdc:templates/context/feature-template.md)

- **Prompts**
  - Action-oriented helpers in `prompts/` used to perform operations
  - Examples: [prompts/create-feature.md](mdc:prompts/create-feature.md), [prompts/update-template.md](mdc:prompts/update-template.md)

- **Agents**
  - Reusable compositions combining persona, workflows, instructions, and output formats
  - Used across prompts; can be embedded with `![[agent-name]]`
  - Example: [agents/dev/lead-developer.md](mdc:agents/dev/lead-developer.md)

